Ownership Contract: Manages property ownership, including transfers and verification of ownership. This contract should handle the creation of new property listings and record each property's current owner.

Transaction Contract: Handles the buying and selling of properties. This includes managing offers, accepting offers, and transferring ownership upon successful transactions. It may also handle escrow mechanisms if needed.

Property Listing Contract: Manages property details, such as location, size, price, and metadata (images, documents). This contract should allow property owners or authorized agents to create and update listings.

Access Control Contract: Manages permissions within the dApp, determining who can list properties, approve transactions, and access certain pieces of information.

Registry Contract: Acts as a central directory for all properties listed on the platform. This contract could help users and external applications discover properties and their corresponding details.
